[{"id":"VR781225","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following statements about the normal force <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub N\"><math alttext=\"F sub N\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>N</mi></msub></math></span></span> of the track exerted on the cart at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>P</mtext></math></span></span> is correct and provides correct justification?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR781225_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A cart of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> rolls down a track and through the circular bottom of the track (Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>P</mtext></math></span></span>) as shown in the figure.</p>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a cart rolling down the left side of a hill toward the circular bottom of the hill, which is indicated as point P.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR781225.g03.svg\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub N equals m g\"><math alttext=\"F sub N equals m g\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>N</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi></mstyle></math></span></span>, because the normal force and the weight of the cart are a Newton’s third law pair.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub N equals m g\"><math alttext=\"F sub N equals m g\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle disp